In [2]:
# Load the dataset
url = "https://covid.ourworldindata.org/data/vaccinations/vaccinations.csv"
data = pd.read_csv(url, nrows=5000)

# Create a list of unique locations for the dropdown
locations = list(data['location'].unique())

# Create an interactive line chart using Altair
chart = alt.Chart(data).mark_line(point=True).encode(
    x=alt.X('date:T',axis=alt.Axis(title='Month')),
    y=alt.Y('total_vaccinations:Q',axis=alt.Axis(title='Total Vaccinations')),
    color='location:N',
    tooltip=['location:N', 'date:T', 'total_vaccinations:Q']
).properties(
    title='COVID-19 Vaccination Progress by Country',
    width=800,
    height=400
).interactive()

# Dropdown for selecting locations
dropdown = alt.binding_select(options=locations)
selection = alt.selection_single(fields=['location'], bind=dropdown, name='Select')

# Apply the selection to the chart
chart = chart.add_selection(selection).transform_filter(selection)

# Display the chart with the dropdown
chart

Out[2]:

In this interactive chart displaying the COVID-19 vaccination progress across various countries, the horizontal axis represents month, while the vertical axis indicates the total number of vaccinations administered. The different colors distinguish between the countries, making it easy to compare their vaccination progress. Moreover, when you hover over the lines or points, a small box appears with specific details about each data point, providing a precise understanding of the vaccination numbers at any given time.The interactive elements play a crucial role in making the chart more useful and engaging. The dropdown menu lets you choose specific countries of interest, allowing for a closer examination of their vaccination journeys. As you select different countries, the chart dynamically updates to display the data for the selected country, enabling you to delve deeper into the vaccination trends and patterns specific to that region. Additionally, the inclusion of individual data points alongside the lines offers a clearer view of the progress over time for each country, facilitating better comparisons and insights into the effectiveness of their vaccination campaigns.
